<paragraph id="1B4D2D3AF54C1871FF65C89939AFFB8E" blockId="4.[163,1072,938,1103]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1509">
N o t e s: Four different subspecies are currently listed for this taxon, all of them occurrying in 
<collectingCountry id="63E56DAAF54C1871FEF2CF7A3B65FBF3" box="[308,381,1052,1074]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="1509">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F6350CBF54C1871FE4BCF7A38BBFBF3" author="NIKODYM M" box="[397,675,1050,1074]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1509" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref18162" refString="NIKODYM M. &amp; A. BEZDEK (2016): Glaphyridae, pp. 87 - 97. - In: LOBL I. E. &amp; D. LOBL (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 3, Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Revised and updated edition. Brill; Leiden, Boston. XXVIII + 983 pp." type="book chapter" year="2016">NIKODÝM &amp; BEZDĚK 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In spite of the recent introduction of one of them (
<bibRefCitation id="7F6350CBF54C1871FEEFCF5F3BACFB8E" author="MITTER H" box="[297,436,1081,1103]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1509" pagination="107 - 112" refId="ref18107" refString="MITTER H. (1990): Vorkommen und Verbreitung einiger Glaphyrus - Arten in Kleinasien. - Koleopterologische Rundschau 60: 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="1990">MITTER 1990</bibRefCitation>
